<body>
<chapter line="1">Kaccāyana <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0001" /> dhātu mañjūsā</chapter>
<centered line="2"> Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa</centered>
<gatha1 line="3">Nirutti nikarā’pāra-pāravāra’ntagaṃ muniṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="4">Vanditvā dhātumañjūsaṃ-brūmi pāvacanañjasaṃ.</gathalast>
<gatha1 line="5">Sogatāgama mā’gamma-taṃ taṃvyākaraṇāni ca,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="6">Pāṭhe cā’paṭhitāpe’ttha dhātvatthā ca pavuccare.</gathalast>
<paragraph line="7">Chanda’hānitthamo’kāraṃ-dhātvantānaṃ <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0002" /> siyākva ci, yūnaṃ dīgho ca dhātumhā-pubbama’tthapadaṃ api.</paragraph>
<hangnum line="8" number="1"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="9"> Bhū sattāyaṃ paca pāke gamusappa gatimhi (ca);</gatha1>
<gathalast line="10">Siloka (dhātu) saṅghāte saki saṅkāya (vattate;).</gathalast>
<hangnum line="11" number="2"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="12"> (Atho) kuka-vakā’dāne ke sadde aki lakkhaṇe;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="13">Ku sadde kucchite ṭaṅka dhāraṇe maki maṇḍane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="14" number="3"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="15"> Vaki koṭillayātrāsu sakka-ṭīkadvayaṃ gate;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="16">Kaki lolattane yāte takī (idha) gatādisu.</gathalast>
<paragraph line="17" number="4"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0003" /> Vava, lokanavittisu cakkhavutimhi (tu) rukkha (ca) khe thirahiṃsakhaṇe niya, mo’panayiṭṭhi vatādisa muṇḍisu dikkha (’tha) kakkha-kakhā hasane tura, hiṃsanavuddhigatīsu (hi) dakkha’danamhi (tu) jakkha (ca) bhakkha (matā) ana, jāladukhesu (tu) dikkha (ca) dukkha (ca) ikkha disa’ṅka na ko’kha suse.</paragraph>
<paragraph line="18" number="5"> [A] nikkha cumbane’(pi) sikkha vijju’pādu’ pāsānamhi rakkha guttivāraṇe (pi) uñchane (siyā’pi) bhikkha yāvaladdhya’laddhisū (pi) vakkha rosasaṃhatesu mokkha muttiyaṃ caje (pi) cikkha vācabodhanesu.</paragraph>
<paragraph line="19">[Ba] <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0004" /> nakha makha rakha naṅkhāmaṅkharakkhī’khīlaṅkhā lakha vakha ikha iṅkhā uṅkha vaṅkhū’kha gatyaṃ vakhi makhi kakhi kaṅkhe khī khaye ukkha seke khu khutadhanisu (vutto) khe(’tha) khāde supe (ca.)</paragraph>
<hangnum line="20" number="6"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="21"> Aggo (tu) gatikoṭille laga saṅge mage’sane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="22">Agī igī rigī ligī vagī gatya’tthadhātavo.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="23" number="7"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="24"> Silāgha katthane jaggha hasane aggha agghane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="25">Sighī āghāyane (hoti) laghi sosagatīsu (ca;).</gathalast>
<hangnum line="26" number="8"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="27"> Vaca byattavace yāca yācane ruca dittiyaṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="28">Suca soke kuca sadde (atho) vica vivecane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="29" number="9"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0005" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="30"> Añca pūjāgate vañca gamane kiñcā’vamaddane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="31">Luñcā’panayane nacca naccane maca rocane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="32" number="10"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="33"> Accā’ccane cu vacane saco (tu) samavāyane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="34">Paca yāte kaci-vacca dittiyaṃ maci dhāraṇe.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="35" number="11"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="36"> Puccha sampucchane muccha mohasmiṃ lañcha lakkhaṇe;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="37">Añchā’yāme (bhave) puñcha puñchane uñcha uñchane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="38" number="12"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="39"> Taccho tanukiraye piñcha piñchane rāja dittiyaṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="40">Vajā’jagamane rañja rāge bhañjā’vamaddane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="41" number="13"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="42"> Añju byattigatīkanti makkhaṇesve’ja kampane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="43">Bhaja saṃsevane sañja saṅge (tu) iñja kampane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="44" number="14"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0006" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="45"> Yaja devaccane dānasaṅgatīkaraṇesu (ca);</gatha1>
<gathalast line="46">Tijakkhamanisānesu dāne(’pi) caja hāniyaṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="47" number="15"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="48"> Sajā’liṅgana vissajja nimmāṇe mujja mujjane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="49">Majja saṃsuddhiyaṃ lajja lajjane tajja tajjane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="50" number="16"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="51"> Ajja-sajjā’jjane sajja nimmāṇe gajja saddane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="52">Guja-kuja dvayaṃ sadde akhyatte khajja bhakkhaṇe.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="53" number="17"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="54"> Bhajja pāke viji bhayacalane vīja vījane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="55">Khajī gamanavekalle jī jaye ju jave (siyā;).</gathalast>
<hangnum line="56" number="18"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="57"> Jhe cintāyujjha ussagge gamane aṭa-paṭa dvayaṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="58">Naṭa nacce raṭa paribhāsane vaṭa veṭhane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="59" number="19"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0007" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="60"> Vaṭṭa āvattane vaṇṭa vaṇṭatthe kaṭa maddane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="61">Phuṭo visaraṇādīsu kaṭa saṃvaraṇe gate.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="62" number="20"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="63"> Ghuṭa ghose patighāte viṭa’kkose (ca) pesane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="64">Bhaṭa bhatyaṃ kuṭa-koṭṭacchedane luṭa loṭane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="65" number="21"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="66"> Jaṭa-jhaṭa-piṭa saṅghāte ciṭu’ttāse ghaṭī’hane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="67">Ghaṭi saṅghaṭṭane taṭṭa cchedane muṭa maddane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="68" number="22"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="69"> Paṭha byattavace heṭha bādhāyaṃ veṭha veṭhane;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="70">Suṭhī-kuṭhī dvayaṃ sose pīṭha hiṃsanadhāraṇe.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="71" number="23"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="72"> Kaṭha sosanapākesu vaṭha thulattane (bhave);</gatha1>
<gathalast line="73">Kaṭhi sose ruṭha-luṭho’paghāte saṭha ketave.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="74" number="24"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0008" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="75"> (Siyā haṭha balakkāre kaḍibhede kaḍicchide;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="76">Maṇḍa vibhūsane caṇḍa caṇḍikke bhaḍi bhaṅḍane.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="77" number="25"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="78"> Paḍi uppaṇḍane liṅgavekalle muḍi khaṇḍane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="79">Gaḍi vatte’kadesamhi gaḍi sannivaye(’pica;);</gathalast>
<hangnum line="80" number="26"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="81"> Raḍi-eraḍi hiṃsāyaṃ piḍi saṅghātaādisu,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="82">Kuḍi dāhe paḍi gate hiḍi āhiṇḍane (siyā;);</gathalast>
<hangnum line="83" number="27"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="84"> Karaṇḍa bhājana’tthamhi (atho) laḍi jigucchane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="85">(Vattate) meḍikoṭille saḍi gumbatthamīraṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="86" number="28"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="87"> (Atho’pi) aḍi aṇḍatthe (dissate) tuḍi toḍane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="88">Vaḍḍha saṃvaḍḍhane kaḍḍha kaḍḍhaṇe bhaṇa bhāsane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="89" number="29"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0009" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="90"> Soṇa vaṇṇe guṇa’bhyāse iṇa-pheṇa dvayaṃ gate,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="91">Paṇa vohārathomesu (vattate) kaṇa milane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="92" number="30"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="93"> Aṇa-raṇa-kaṇa-muṇa-kvaṇa-kuṇa sadde,</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="94">Yata patiyatane juta dittimhi;</gatha2>
<gatha3 line="95">Ata-pata gamane cita saññāṇe,</gatha3>
<gathalast line="96">Kita vāsā’do vatu vattumhi.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="97" number="31"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="98"> (Bhave) kattha silāghāyaṃ matha-mattha viloḷane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="99">Nātha yācanasantāpa isserā’siṃsanesu (ca;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="100" number="32"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="101"> Putha (ce) puthu vitthāre byatha bhīticalesu (ca),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="102">Gotthu vaṃse patha-pantha gate nanda samiddhiyaṃ;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="103" number="33"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="104"> Vandā’bhivādathomesu gada byattavace’(pica),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="105">(Atho) ninda garahāyaṃ khadi pakkhandanādisu;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="106" number="34"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0010" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="107"> Edī (tu) kiñcicalena cadi kantihiḷādane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="108">Kilidī paridevādo udissavakiledane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="109" number="35"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="110"> Idī (tu) paramissariye adiandu (ca) bandhane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="111">Bhaganda sevane (hoti) bhadda kalyāṇakammani;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="112" number="36"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="113"> Sida siṅgārapākesu sadduharitasosane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="114">Madi balye muda-madā santose madda maddane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="115" number="37"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="116"> Sandu passavanādīsu kanda’vhāne (ca’) rodane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="117">Vida lābhe dada dāne rudi assuvimocane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="118" number="38"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="119"> Sado visaraṇā’dānagamane (cā’)vasādane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="120">Hiḷāda (tu) sukhe sūdakkharaṇe rada vilekhaṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="121" number="39"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="122"> Sāda assādanādīsu gada byattavace’(pica),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="123">Nada abyattasadde (tu) radā’dā-khāda-bhakkhaṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="124" number="40"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0011" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="125"> Adda yācanayātrādisva (tho) mida sinehane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="126">(Siyā) khuda jigacchāyaṃ daḷidda duggaccaṃ (hi tu;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="127" number="41"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="128"> Dā dave du gatīvuddhayaṃ dā dāne vida jānane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="129">Tadi ālasiye bādha bādhāyaṃ gudha kīḷane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="130" number="42"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="131"> (Atho) gādha patiṭṭhāyaṃ vuṭhu-edha (ca) vuddhiyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="132">Dhā (hoti) dhāraṇe (ceva) cintāyaṃ budha bodhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="133" number="43"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="134"> Sidhu gatimhi yudha sampahāre vidha vedhane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="135">Rādha hiṃsāyasaṃrādhe badha-bandha (ca) bandhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="136" number="44"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="137"> Sidha-sādha (ca) siddhimhi dhe pāne indha dittiyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="138">Māna pūjāya vana-sana sambhave ana pāṇane;</gatha2>
<gathalast line="139">Kana dittigatīkantyaṃ khana-khanva’vadāraṇe.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="140" number="45"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0012" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="141"> Gupa gopanake gupa saṃvaraṇe tapa santāpe tapa issariye,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="142">Cupa mandagate tapuubbege rapa-lapa vākye sapa akkose;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="143" number="46"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="144"> Japa-jappa vace’byatte tappa santappane (siyā),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="145">Kapi kiñcicale kappa sāmatthe vepu kampane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="146" number="47"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="147"> Tappa santagatecchede takke hiṃsādisu’(ccate),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="148">Vapa bījavinikkhepe dhūpa santapane’(pi ca);</gathalast>
<hangnum line="149" number="48"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="150"> Capa sāntve pu pavane jhapa dāhe supo saye,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="151">Puppha vikasane (hoti) ramba’lambavasaṃsane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="152" number="49"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="153"> Cumba vadanasaṃyoge kamba saṃvaraṇe (mato),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="154">Amba sadde (ca) assāde tāyane sabi maṇḍane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="155" number="50"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0013" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="156"> Gabba dappe’bba-sabbā’(pi) gamane pubba pūraṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="157">Gumba’bbagumbane cabba adane ubba dhāraṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="158" number="51"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="159"> Labha lābhe jambha gattavināme subha sobhane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="160">Bhī bhaye rabha rābhasse (cā)’rambhe khubha sañcale;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="161" number="52"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="162"> Thambha-khambha patibandhe gabbha pāgabbhiye vadhe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="163">Sumbha saṃsumbhane sambha vissāse yabha methune;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="164" number="53"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="165"> Dubha jīgiṃsane dabbha ganthane udrabhā’dane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="166">Kamū (tu) padavikkhepe khamū (tu) sahaṇe (siyā;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="167" number="54"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="168"> Bhamu anavaṭṭhāne (ca) vamu uggiraṇādisu,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="169">Kilamu-klamū gelaññe ramu kīḷā’ya (mīrito;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="170" number="55"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="171"> Damo dame nama name (atho) sama parissame,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="172">Yamu uparame nāse ama yāte mu bandhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="173" number="56"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0014" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="174"> Dhamo pumo (ca) dhamane tama saṅkāvibhūsane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="175">Dhuma-thīma (ca) saṅghāte tama sāntva’vasādiye;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="176" number="57"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="177"> Ayo vayo paya-mayo nayo rayagatimhi (ca)</gatha1>
<gathalast line="178">Daya dānagatīrakkhā hiṃsādisu yu missane;</gathalast>
<gatha1 line="179">Cāya sampūjane tāya santāne pāya vuddhiyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="180">(Atho) usūya dosā’vikaraṇe sāya sāyane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="181" number="58"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="182"> Tara taraṇasmiṃ thara santharaṇe bhara bharaṇasmiṃ phara sampharaṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="183">Sara gati cintā hiṃsā sadde phura calanādo hara haraṇasmiṃ;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="184" number="59"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="185"> Ri santatismiṃ ri gate ru sadde khuracchidasmiṃ dhara dhāraṇamhi,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="186">Jara jīraṇatthe marapāṇacāge khara sekanāse ghara sevanamhi;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="187" number="60"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0015" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="188"> Garo nigareṇa seke dara ḍāhe vidāraṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="189">Cara gatibhakkhaṇesu vara saṃvaraṇādisu;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="190" number="61"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="191"> Caracchede aranāse gate (ca) pūra pūraṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="192">Kura kkose nara naye jāgara supinakkhaye;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="193" number="62"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="194"> Pīlu-palū-sala-hulā gatya’tthā cala kampane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="195">Khala sañcalane phulla vikāse jala dittiyaṃ;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="196" number="63"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="197"> Phala nipphattiyaṃ (hoti) dala dittividāraṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="198">Dala duggatiyaṃ nīla vaṇṇe mīla nimīlane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="199" number="64"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="200"> Sila samādhimhi kīla bandhe gala-gilā’dane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="201">Kūla āvaraṇe sūla rujāyaṃ balapāṇane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="202" number="65"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="203"> Tala-mūla patiṭṭhāyaṃ vala-valla nivāraṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="204">Palla ninne (ca) gamane mala-malla’vadhāraṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="205" number="66"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0016" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="206"> (Vattate) khila kāṭhinne kalile ala-kala dvayaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="207">Vella sañcalane kalla sajjane alibandhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="208" number="67"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="209"> Culla hāvakiraye thūlā’kassane cūla maddane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="210">(Vattate) khala soceyyo pala rakkhagatesu(pi;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="211" number="68"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="212"> Kela-khela-cela-pela-vela-sañcalanādisu,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="213">Ava rakkhaṇe jīva pāṇadhāraṇe (tu) plavo gate;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="214" number="69"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="215"> Kaṇḍuvanamhi kaṇḍuvo saraṇe chedane dave,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="216">Davo (tu) davane devu devane sevu sevane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="217" number="70"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="218"> Dhāva gamanavuddhimhi (paṭhito) dhovu dhovane;</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="219">Ve-vī dve tantusantāne ve-vu saṃvaraṇe (siyā)</gatha2>
<gathalast line="220">Hve avhāne keva seke dhuva yātrā thiresu (ca;);</gathalast>
<hangnum line="221" number="71"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0017" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="222"> Asa gasa adane ghasa adanasmiṃ-isa pariyese isuicchāyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="223">Sasu pāṇanagatihiṃsā’dya’tthe-masa āmasane musa sammose;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="224" number="72"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="225"> Kusa akkose dusa appīte-tusa santose pusa posamhi,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="226">Rusa ālepe rusa hiṃsāyaṃ-masu macchere usu dāhe (’pi;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="227" number="73"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="228"> Hasa hasanasmiṃ ghusa saddasmiṃ-tasa ubbege trasa ubbege,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="229">Lasa kantya’tthe rasa assāde-(puna)bhasa bhasmikaraṇe(cā’pi;)</gathalast>
<hangnum line="230" number="74"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="231"> Gavesa maggaṇe paṃsa nāsane disa pekkhaṇe,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="232">Sāsā’nusiṭṭhiyaṃ haṃsa pitiyaṃ pāsa bandhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="233" number="75"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="234"> Saṃsa pasaṃsane issa issāyaṃ kassa kassane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="235">Dhaṃsa padhaṃsane siṃsa icchāyaṃ ghaṃsa ghaṃsane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="236" number="76"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0018" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="237"> Saṃsa-daṃsā (tu) ḍasane bhāsa vācāya dittiyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="238">(Siyā) bhusa alaṅkāre (atho) āsū’pavesane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="239" number="77"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="240"> Vasa kantinivāsesu vassasecanasaddane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="241">Kisa sāṇe kasa gate kasa hiṃsāvilekhane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="242" number="78"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="243"> Disā’tisajjanā’dīsu kāsa dittimhi sajjane,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="244">(Duve dhātu) khasa-jhasa hiṃsāyaṃ misa milane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="245" number="79"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="246"> Su hiṃsākulasandhānayātrā’dīsu su passave,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="247">Su sadde su pasavane si saye (ca) si sevane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="248" number="80"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="249"> Maha pūjāyā’rahapūjāyaṃ-guha saṃvaraṇe liha assāde,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="250">Raha cāgasmiṃ muha mucchāyaṃ-maha sattāyaṃ bahu saṃkhyāne;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="251" number="81"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0019" /></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="252"> Saha khame daha bhasmikaraṇe (ca) patiṭṭhāyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gathalast line="253">Ruha sañjanane ūha vitakke vaha pāpaṇe;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="254" number="82"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="255"> Duha’ppapūraṇe nāse diho upacaye (mato),</gatha1>
<gathalast line="256">Nindāyaṃ garaho īha ghaṭṭane miha sevane;</gathalast>
<hangnum line="257" number="83"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="258"> Gāha viloḷane brūha-baha-braha (ca) vuddhiyaṃ,</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="259">Vhe saddamhi hasane hā cāge luḷa manthane</gatha2>
<gathalast line="260">Kīḷavihāramhi laḷa vilāse’(mesavuddhikā;)</gathalast>
